column5: Well This year was the year of the PB'S  Mike my Good OL' PAL.  Scored His PB Small Mouth Bass.  4.2 lbs on the DIG.      Congrats BUDDY!  Oh yeah and I scored a Beauty of a BRONZEBACK!      Almost Flipped the Boat to get this shot ....  But it was worth it.    Less than 10 bass were caught.  But sure was a Nice relaxing day on the calm fall water.    enjoi.
Nice looking bronze you guys got into! Looks like a really nice place to spend a few hours. Great shots!
Beauties Kev WHAT A PIG!!!!  Congrats to Mike on that HAWG  Great job you guys, but have to ask you.... any muski fishing lately or on the horizon??? Jacques

we went 2-3 times with a BIG SKUNK fallowing us.  this week end its stephanies birthday. so forget about the fish'n i was lucky to get out today.  but for the next week ends until ice we are going musky fishing.  we should all go.  you and paul  me and ryan.  hit the big girls!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Cool Kev Sometimes it happens, but I guess you still had a good time out in the boat!!! Sounds like a plan     This weekend it's deer hunting for me, closing season coming to an end I'm still hopeful.... spending time in the bush is what the doctor ordered Jacques
Some real nice smallies there congrats on the PB's  , heading out tomorrow with a buddy Richard
